'''Bergepolis''' ({{lang-grc|Βεργέπολις}}) was a [[ancient Greek|Greek]] town located in [[ancient Thrace]], in the region between the river Nestos to the river Hebros. It was founded by colonists from [[Abdera, Thrace|Abdera]].<ref name=Poleis>{{cite book|author= Mogens Herman Hansen & Thomas Heine Nielsen |title= An inventory of archaic and classical poleis|year= 2004|publisher= [[Oxford University Press]]|location=New York|isbn= 0-19-814099-1|chapter= Thrace from Nestos to Hebros|page= 877}}</ref> Bergepolis was an urban center dependent on Abdera. Bergepolis survived in the Roman times.<ref name=Poleis/> 

Its site is located {{convert|9|miles}} southeast of modern [[Xanthi]].<ref>{{Cite Barrington|51}}</ref><ref>{{Cite DARE|32308}}</ref>

